# API & Integration Patterns

## LLM — OpenAI primary, Groq silent fallback

```typescript
async function getAnalysis(systemPrompt: string, transcript: string): Promise<string> {
  try {
    const response = await openai.chat.completions.create({
      model: 'gpt-4o',
      messages: [
        { role: 'system', content: systemPrompt },
        { role: 'user', content: transcript },
      ],
      max_tokens: 200,
    })
    return response.choices[0].message.content ?? ''
  } catch {
    const fallback = await groq.chat.completions.create({
      model: 'llama-3.3-70b-versatile',
      messages: [
        { role: 'system', content: systemPrompt },
        { role: 'user', content: transcript },
      ],
    })
    return fallback.choices[0].message.content ?? ''
  }
}
```

- Run three card analyses in parallel: `Promise.all([...])`
- Keep feedback to 4–5 sentences (saves ElevenLabs TTS credits)

## ElevenLabs Speech-to-Text

- `POST https://api.elevenlabs.io/v1/speech-to-text`
- Header: `xi-api-key: process.env.ELEVENLABS_API_KEY`
- Body (FormData): `model_id=scribe_v1`, `file=(audio blob)`
- Returns: `{ text: "transcript" }`

## ElevenLabs Text-to-Speech

- `POST https://api.elevenlabs.io/v1/text-to-speech/{voiceId}`
- Headers: `xi-api-key`, `Content-Type: application/json`, `Accept: audio/mpeg`
- Body: `{ text, model_id: "eleven_multilingual_v2" }`
- Return binary as `Response` with `Content-Type: audio/mpeg`

